  "text": "The included retrospective trials were evaluated by 2 authors (BCW and LLS) and their results assessed using 9 star Newcastle-Ottawa scale. [CITATION_1] The Newcastle-Ottawa scale assesses trial quality by evaluating 3 domains: selection, comparability, and outcome for cohort studies or exposure for case-control studies. Selection and outcome or exposure domain that meets the criteria is given a star, while the comparability domain has a maximum of 2 stars. The maximum of stars is 9 points; scores 7 to 9 points were defined as high quality and scores <7 as low quality studies.",
